WEBVTT

00:02.461 --> 00:03.795
Previously on
<i>"The Girl from Plainville"...</i>

00:03.795 --> 00:04.838
You called in
a missing person?

00:04.838 --> 00:06.715
Name's Conrad Roy III.

00:06.715 --> 00:09.968
<i>What's your son driving?</i>
Ford F250, black.

00:09.968 --> 00:13.055
- There's yellow tape
around our son's truck.

00:13.055 --> 00:14.431
Michelle, what is it?

00:14.431 --> 00:15.724
- Conrad's dead.

00:15.724 --> 00:16.934
- Who's Conrad?

00:16.934 --> 00:18.727

<i>Michelle Carter. Know her?</i>

00:18.727 --> 00:19.895
<i>Not really.</i>

00:19.895 --> 00:21.146
- They were dating?

00:21.146 --> 00:22.981
- They only met up, like,
once or twice.

00:22.981 --> 00:24.566
- Florida?
That's where you guys met?

00:24.566 --> 00:28.987
I remember that trip.
He came back happy.

00:28.987 --> 00:30.530
He left you a note, sweetheart.

00:30.530 --> 00:33.116
- He did?
Well, can I read it?

00:33.116 --> 00:35.327
- I was thinking of putting
something together for Coco,

00:35.327 --> 00:36.870
for, like, mental health
or something.

00:36.870 --> 00:38.747
- I would be honored.

01:32.009 --> 01:33.719
Dinner is at 5:00 sharp
every night,

01:33.719 --> 01:35.554
and don't be late,
or you'll be eating crumbs.

01:35.554 --> 01:36.597
- Okay.
- Come on!

01:38.140 --> 01:40.309
Coco, come on, help me.

01:42.519 --> 01:44.187
Bags aren't gonna grow legs.

01:44.187 --> 01:45.689
Move it.

02:28.482 --> 02:30.525
Getting really
good grades,

02:30.525 --> 02:31.943
doing really, really well.
They're both doing great.

02:31.943 --> 02:33.195
- Yeah, but no,
she's bad at it.

02:33.195 --> 02:34.488
- All right.
- Shut up.

02:34.488 --> 02:35.614
- What?
You suck.

02:35.614 --> 02:37.449
- Sydney!
- Hey, he does too.

02:38.033 --> 02:40.077
- All right, that's enough.

02:40.077 --> 02:41.870
Math wasn't my thing
either.

02:43.955 --> 02:45.749
- Hey, put it down.

02:47.584 --> 02:49.961
There's a new girlfriend.
She's from...

02:51.755 --> 02:53.048
- Ohio.
- Ohio.

02:53.048 --> 02:54.508
- How nice.
Is she pretty?

02:54.508 --> 02:56.093
- We don't know.
They met on the computer.

02:56.093 --> 02:57.302
- Dad.

02:57.302 --> 02:58.553
- Hey, listen, by the way,
your mom says

02:58.553 --> 02:59.930
you can't go visit her.

02:59.930 --> 03:01.264
- What?

03:01.264 --> 03:03.183
- Yeah, Coco, her dad
doesn't even know you.

03:03.183 --> 03:04.434
- Mom said
she would talk to him.

03:04.434 --> 03:07.145
- And she did talk to him,
and he said no.

03:08.897 --> 03:10.857
You've got a problem with it,
talk to your mom, all right?

03:10.857 --> 03:12.818
I'm just the messenger
this time.

03:17.572 --> 03:19.366
- Is baseball good?

03:19.366 --> 03:21.702
- It's off-season,
so it's in the spring.

03:22.619 --> 03:24.079
- How do you like
your new school?

03:24.079 --> 03:25.247
- He dropped out.
- What?

03:25.247 --> 03:26.790
- Oh, my gosh.
- You dropped out?

03:26.790 --> 03:28.291
- Will you put something
in your mouth?

03:28.291 --> 03:32.295
- I--I didn't drop out.
I'm just doing online classes.

03:32.295 --> 03:34.673
- Yeah, he does everything from
the computer right from home.

03:34.673 --> 03:36.133
So it's still school.

03:36.133 --> 03:37.968
I just don't have to deal
with stupid people.

03:37.968 --> 03:39.261
- That's nice.

03:39.261 --> 03:40.887
- And I've been taking him
to work with me too.

03:40.887 --> 03:42.722
Yeah, he's doing great.
We go out, you know,

03:42.722 --> 03:45.225
three weeks out,
a couple days in.

03:45.225 --> 03:49.104
- Is this the famous Roy clan?
- Indeed, it is.

03:49.104 --> 03:50.939
- All she does
is gush about you.

03:50.939 --> 03:52.607
Ruth lives a few houses down.

03:52.607 --> 03:54.526
This is my nephew, Conrad Jr.

03:54.526 --> 03:56.236
- Hi, call me Co.

03:56.987 --> 04:00.157
Your tugboat towed Sully
in off the Hudson.

04:00.157 --> 04:03.285
- Oh, that was just, you know,
right place, right time.

04:03.285 --> 04:05.662
And this is
his beautiful wife, Carolyn.

04:05.662 --> 04:07.122
- She's--
- Actually, we're not--

04:07.122 --> 04:10.459
- And these are the kids,
Paige and Sydney and Coco,

04:10.459 --> 04:12.836
who is quite
the baseball player.

04:12.836 --> 04:15.088
My granddaughter
plays softball.

04:15.088 --> 04:16.423
Oh.

04:16.423 --> 04:18.925
- He's also working
in the family business.

04:18.925 --> 04:22.220
- Such a beautiful
and talented family.

04:22.220 --> 04:24.264
Right to be proud.

04:25.182 --> 04:26.600
- Nice to meet you.

04:28.977 --> 04:30.437
She's nice.

04:30.437 --> 04:31.688
You guys are lucky.

04:31.688 --> 04:35.525
I mean, this food
is incredible.

05:13.647 --> 05:16.024
Hey, it's Lily.
<i>Leave me a message.</i>

05:16.024 --> 05:17.818
- Are you ghosting me?

05:18.902 --> 05:20.403
I don't care
what your dad thinks.

05:20.403 --> 05:22.197
Call me back.

05:34.084 --> 05:36.169
Hey, it's Lily,
<i>leave me a message.</i>

05:39.589 --> 05:44.427
- I'm sorry.
I'm just pissed off...

05:44.427 --> 05:47.806
not at you.

05:47.806 --> 05:49.015
Just call me, please.

05:59.442 --> 06:01.152
Coco.

06:01.152 --> 06:02.571
Come here.

06:13.832 --> 06:15.792
This is my granddaughter,
Michelle.

06:16.710 --> 06:18.211
Michelle, this is Coco.

06:18.211 --> 06:20.255
- Conrad.
- What?

06:21.631 --> 06:23.925
- Conrad Henri Roy III.

06:25.051 --> 06:27.220
This is the young man
I was telling you about.

06:27.220 --> 06:29.055
Lives in Mattapoisett.

06:30.432 --> 06:31.892
- Hi.

06:31.892 --> 06:34.144
Michelle lives
in Plainville.

06:34.144 --> 06:35.395
What are the chances?

06:36.855 --> 06:38.189
- Cool.

06:38.189 --> 06:40.358
She's here
for a couple more days.

06:40.358 --> 06:42.819
Thought you two could hang.

06:42.819 --> 06:45.530
I'm gonna go wrangle the gear.
Be right back.

06:52.078 --> 06:53.413
- Grandma.

06:56.958 --> 06:58.376
Where's Mattapoisett?

06:59.544 --> 07:01.171
- South Coast.

07:02.130 --> 07:04.841
- I've heard stuff about it.

07:04.841 --> 07:06.509
- Stuff?

07:07.135 --> 07:08.970
- That's it's rough.

07:10.555 --> 07:11.848
- Hmm.

07:17.604 --> 07:19.689
I gotta go.

07:19.689 --> 07:20.899
Hey.

07:20.899 --> 07:22.692

<i>This is Lily's dad.</i>

07:22.692 --> 07:24.986
<i>I thought I was very clear</i>
<i>with your mom.</i>

07:27.030 --> 07:28.365
- Can I just please--

07:28.365 --> 07:30.283
Stop calling
<i>or we'll have a problem.</i>

07:48.802 --> 07:50.345
- What do you think?

07:50.345 --> 07:53.348
- They're just texts,
a lot of goddamn texts.

07:53.348 --> 07:56.059
- Due respect,
those are fucked-up texts.

07:57.936 --> 08:00.522
- Was there
a missing person's report?

08:00.522 --> 08:01.564
- Yeah.
Put out a BOLO

08:01.564 --> 08:03.608
even though it was just
12 hours.

08:03.608 --> 08:06.027
Did he deal
with depression at all?

08:06.027 --> 08:07.237
- Yeah.

08:07.237 --> 08:09.781
Was this
his first suicide attempt?

08:09.781 --> 08:11.241
- No.

08:11.241 --> 08:14.035
So how's this girl
responsible this time?

08:15.245 --> 08:20.917
- Look, her texts to him get
even more insistent

08:20.917 --> 08:22.377
in the final 24 hours.

08:22.377 --> 08:24.671
And according to the records,
they spoke on the phone

08:24.671 --> 08:26.965
for 42 minutes before he died.

08:26.965 --> 08:28.383
Last person to talk to him.

08:29.551 --> 08:30.927
- Her statement?

08:30.927 --> 08:32.512
- Haven't gotten one yet.

08:33.763 --> 08:35.306
- So what do you want?

08:35.306 --> 08:37.517
- A warrant for her phone.

08:41.479 --> 08:43.273
Okay, look.

08:47.694 --> 08:50.780
She says,
"You keep pushing it off,

08:50.780 --> 08:52.449
"and you say you'll do it,
but you never do.

08:52.449 --> 08:56.619
"It's always gonna be that way
if you don't take action.

08:56.619 --> 08:59.539
"You're just making it harder
on yourself by pushing it off.

08:59.539 --> 09:01.833
You just have to do it."

09:04.753 --> 09:08.089
- Bring me something that can
prove intent, contradiction,

09:08.089 --> 09:10.717
even a cover-up,
and we'll talk.

09:10.717 --> 09:12.385
You haven't got it yet.

10:09.150 --> 10:10.235
Cass, I saw your Insta.

10:10.235 --> 10:12.070
You went
to the Keith Urban concert?

10:12.070 --> 10:14.364
- Yeah, it was amazing.
- It was so fun.

10:14.364 --> 10:15.698
We were, like, five rows back--

10:15.698 --> 10:18.660
- So it's my birthday
this weekend.

10:18.660 --> 10:21.496
I was thinking we could go
maybe into Boston,

10:21.496 --> 10:24.332
do dinner.
It could be really fun.

10:24.332 --> 10:25.959
Maybe we could get
matching tattoos.

10:25.959 --> 10:28.044
I'll be 18,
so I could get one.

10:28.044 --> 10:31.589
- Yeah.
Um, that sounds so fun,

10:31.589 --> 10:33.675
uh, but I think
I'm working that night.

10:33.675 --> 10:35.635
Yeah, I have to check
with my parents.

10:35.635 --> 10:37.220
- Mm-hmm. Same.

10:38.429 --> 10:39.597
- Sure.

10:43.351 --> 10:45.019
I was thinking
we could've talked

10:45.019 --> 10:48.148
about the fundraiser.

10:48.148 --> 10:50.316
I'm gonna call it
"Homers for Conrad."

10:51.025 --> 10:52.610
You guys said
that you would help me,

10:52.610 --> 10:54.404
but if you're too busy,
it's totally fine.

10:54.404 --> 10:57.448
I--I can plan it on my own.
It's not really a big deal.

10:57.448 --> 10:59.701
- That's what you want to do
for your birthday?

11:01.786 --> 11:03.705
- Yeah.
Is that weird?

11:03.705 --> 11:08.168
- No, no, it's just,
you should be celebrating.

11:11.421 --> 11:13.798
- I just really want
to get it right for Conrad.

11:15.508 --> 11:17.802
Sometimes I feel
like he's here with me.

11:18.511 --> 11:20.471
I don't want to let him down.

11:24.309 --> 11:25.768
- You know what?

11:25.768 --> 11:29.314
I could probably get someone
to cover my shift, right?

11:29.314 --> 11:31.232
Yeah, oh yeah,
for sure.

11:32.692 --> 11:34.068
- Thanks.

12:46.683 --> 12:48.184
- Hi.

12:48.184 --> 12:49.769
Sorry, I didn't--

12:49.769 --> 12:52.105
- It's okay.
Just wasn't expecting anyone.

12:53.481 --> 12:55.275
Conrad, right?

12:57.568 --> 12:58.820
- Sorry, you are, um...

12:58.820 --> 13:00.863
- Michelle.
- Right, right.

13:02.240 --> 13:03.616
See you later.

13:03.616 --> 13:05.451
- Oh, okay, cool.

13:11.416 --> 13:13.293
- I know a trick
that helps me sleep.

13:14.919 --> 13:16.671
- Works great.

13:20.717 --> 13:22.468
- I could teach it to you
if you want.

13:23.636 --> 13:25.388
- Sure.

13:28.641 --> 13:29.767
- Turtle.

13:30.852 --> 13:32.437
- What?

13:32.437 --> 13:33.896
You have to say
the first thing

13:33.896 --> 13:34.939
that pops into your head.
- Oh.

13:34.939 --> 13:36.232
- It's a word game.

13:36.232 --> 13:37.483
Eventually,
your brain just drifts,

13:37.483 --> 13:39.444
trying to think
of a random word.

13:39.444 --> 13:41.904
- So basically, you're
boring yourself to sleep.

13:45.825 --> 13:47.785
- Turtle.

13:49.996 --> 13:51.497
- Ninja.

13:51.497 --> 13:53.666
- Ninja turtles?
Really?

13:53.666 --> 13:56.586
- It's the first thing
that came to my mind.

13:58.129 --> 13:59.964
What would you have said?

13:59.964 --> 14:02.008
- Like, pizza.

14:02.008 --> 14:04.844
- Dude, that--
that is ninja turtles.

14:07.680 --> 14:09.557
Okay, bread.

14:09.557 --> 14:11.476
- Cheese.

14:11.476 --> 14:13.311
- Mouse.

14:13.311 --> 14:16.439
- Ratatouille.
- Chef.

14:16.439 --> 14:17.857
- Ratatouille.

14:17.857 --> 14:20.026
- No, you can't say
the same word.

14:20.026 --> 14:23.154
- So many rules.
Um...

14:23.154 --> 14:24.530
Disney.

14:25.990 --> 14:27.658
- Princess.

14:28.743 --> 14:29.827
- Prince.

14:32.663 --> 14:34.415
- Romance.

14:37.668 --> 14:39.003
- Kiss.

14:43.424 --> 14:44.759
- Girl.

14:47.720 --> 14:49.138
- Pretty.

17:39.559 --> 17:41.102
Ten, nine...

17:51.404 --> 17:52.613
- How you holding up?

17:54.407 --> 17:57.535
- People ask me that like
there's gonna be a good answer.

17:58.202 --> 18:01.038
- I guess maybe people
don't know what to say.

18:01.914 --> 18:03.708
- You can say nothing.

18:06.502 --> 18:08.921
- Yeah.
Um, okay.

18:08.921 --> 18:12.592
Uh, look, I--I just have,
um, a--a couple questions

18:12.592 --> 18:14.385
to close the case.

18:14.385 --> 18:16.596
Um, just routine.

18:16.596 --> 18:19.724
Did your son have, um,
a computer?

18:19.724 --> 18:22.768
- Yeah.
It's at his dad's.

18:22.768 --> 18:24.520
- Can I get it?

18:24.520 --> 18:28.149
It would be helpful,
tie up some loose ends.

18:28.149 --> 18:30.568
Like I said, it's--it's just
something we do.

18:30.568 --> 18:32.403
- Are your loose ends
gonna tell me

18:32.403 --> 18:33.863
why what happened happened?

18:39.785 --> 18:44.665
- Do you have--do you have
any sense, any--any idea?

18:44.665 --> 18:46.292
- I mean, how many kids
you know spend a day

18:46.292 --> 18:48.711
on the beach with their moms
and then go kill themselves?

18:54.133 --> 18:55.926
Mine did.

19:01.474 --> 19:04.685
I--I gotta swing by there
to drop the girls off.

19:04.685 --> 19:06.646
I can--I can get the laptop.

19:07.355 --> 19:08.356
Um, okay.

19:08.356 --> 19:09.649
I, um--I don't want to cause

19:09.649 --> 19:11.942
any, you know, strife.

19:11.942 --> 19:14.195
- It's all fucking strife.

19:14.195 --> 19:15.446
- Better for me to go?

19:15.446 --> 19:17.448
- A cop
showing up unannounced?

19:18.616 --> 19:19.992
Definitely not better.

19:22.828 --> 19:24.789
Okay, well,
the brisket looks good.

19:24.789 --> 19:26.290
It looks amazing.

19:26.290 --> 19:27.458
Oh, look.

19:27.458 --> 19:28.417
Did you bring me my beers?

19:28.417 --> 19:29.627
Yes.

19:38.886 --> 19:40.054
Here they are.

19:40.054 --> 19:41.305
- Hi, Grandma.
- Hi.

19:41.305 --> 19:43.891
Hey.
Come here, you guys.

19:43.891 --> 19:47.103
Ah!
Sydney.

19:47.103 --> 19:49.355
Hi.

19:51.190 --> 19:52.191
Uh, you better be hungry.

19:52.191 --> 19:53.442
Grab a plate.

19:53.442 --> 19:54.860
- Yeah, what about you, Lynn?
You hungry?

19:54.860 --> 19:56.195
- I'm not staying.

19:56.195 --> 19:57.780
- Conrad, get her a plate.

19:57.780 --> 19:59.407
- She said she ain't staying.

19:59.407 --> 20:01.534
- Well, look at her.
She needs to eat.

20:01.534 --> 20:03.285
- Well, we'll have to do
some rationing.

20:03.285 --> 20:05.037
I didn't plan
for an extra body.

20:05.037 --> 20:06.414
Look, it's fine.

20:06.414 --> 20:08.040
I'd hate
for y'all to go hungry.

20:08.040 --> 20:11.377
- See?
It all works out.

20:11.377 --> 20:12.670
- Hey.

20:12.670 --> 20:13.671
Hey.

20:13.671 --> 20:16.006
- How you doing?

20:16.006 --> 20:18.300
You saw they brought
Coco's truck back?

20:18.300 --> 20:19.677
- Yeah.
Can I--

20:19.677 --> 20:23.305
- They also brought that, um--
that water pump too.

20:24.390 --> 20:25.516
I didn't know
what to do with it.

20:25.516 --> 20:27.101
I put it in the garage.
It's like--

20:27.101 --> 20:28.477
- Can we not talk
about that now?

20:28.477 --> 20:29.770
- Yeah.
Sorry.

20:29.770 --> 20:32.231
- Look, I--I need
your house key.

20:32.231 --> 20:33.941
How come?

20:33.941 --> 20:36.026
- The detective wants
Coco's laptop,

20:36.026 --> 20:39.655
something about closing up
the investigation.

20:39.655 --> 20:41.615
- Why didn't he just call me?

20:41.615 --> 20:43.075
- Well, you can call
and ask him,

20:43.075 --> 20:45.035
or you can just give me
the key.

20:45.035 --> 20:46.662
- Don't you think
that's a little weird?

20:46.662 --> 20:47.955
- No, I don't.

20:49.248 --> 20:50.374
Come on, Lynn.

20:50.374 --> 20:52.168
I can't just give you
my house key.

20:52.168 --> 20:53.627
- It'll take two minutes.

20:53.627 --> 20:56.297
- Put yourself in my shoes.
- In your shoes?

20:56.297 --> 20:57.882
You're in my house
all the goddamn time.

20:57.882 --> 20:59.383
- Not by myself, I'm not
in your house all the time.

20:59.383 --> 21:00.551
- Jesus Christ,
what, do you think

21:00.551 --> 21:01.635
I'm gonna snoop around?
- All right.

21:01.635 --> 21:03.179
Keep it down.
Just calm down.

21:03.179 --> 21:04.472
- I divorced you.
- Co, Co,

21:04.472 --> 21:05.806
just get her the keys.

21:05.806 --> 21:06.974
Have you guys seen this?

21:07.558 --> 21:10.352
Michelle's hosting
a baseball tournament for Coco.

21:10.352 --> 21:12.229
Michelle?
Who's Michelle?

21:12.938 --> 21:15.232
- Coco's friend
from Plainville, that girl.

21:15.232 --> 21:17.401
- Oh, right.
- I think it's weird.

21:17.401 --> 21:19.653
She's just trying to do
something nice for Coco

21:19.653 --> 21:20.905
and for us.

21:20.905 --> 21:23.073
- So what?
Are you gonna go to this?

21:23.073 --> 21:25.868
- What, you're not?
- I don't know.

21:25.868 --> 21:27.912
Dad, you want to go?

21:28.579 --> 21:29.872
Huh?

21:29.872 --> 21:31.373
They're having
a baseball tournament

21:31.373 --> 21:32.833
in Plainville for Coco.

21:32.833 --> 21:34.210
- Plainville?

21:34.210 --> 21:35.836
- Yeah, Coco's friend.
She lives up there.

21:35.836 --> 21:37.797
- It's
a little fundraiser thing.

21:37.797 --> 21:40.216
- A fundraiser?
Who do you think we are?

21:40.216 --> 21:41.926
We're like we need
a goddamn handout?

21:41.926 --> 21:43.636
- Dad.
- It's not a fundraiser for us.

21:43.636 --> 21:45.095
They're...

21:45.095 --> 21:47.890
they're donating the money
to mental health awareness.

21:47.890 --> 21:49.433
- The hell's that mean?

21:51.018 --> 21:52.353
- Like, suicide awareness.

21:53.562 --> 21:55.940
- You fucking kidding me?
- All right, Dad--

21:55.940 --> 21:57.358
This is how you
want to honor your son,

21:57.358 --> 21:58.442
by saying he was crazy?

21:58.442 --> 21:59.860
- How is this about me?

21:59.860 --> 22:01.153
- Dad, she didn't have anything
to do with this.

22:01.153 --> 22:03.072
- Mental health awareness.
- Co?

22:03.072 --> 22:04.073
You got some nerve, Lynn.

22:04.073 --> 22:05.241
All right, Conrad--

22:05.241 --> 22:06.283
- Dad, come on--
- You've got some nerve.

22:06.283 --> 22:07.743
You never even took Coco
to church.

22:07.743 --> 22:08.911
- All right, that's enough.
Mom, you gotta do something.

22:08.911 --> 22:10.246
- Your kids wouldn't know
the Lord's Prayer

22:10.246 --> 22:12.748
