25:11.844 --> 25:13.262
- Seriously, Sydney, shut up.

25:13.262 --> 25:14.930
- You shut up.

25:14.930 --> 25:16.390
- I have a sister
about your age.

25:16.390 --> 25:18.183
- She an asshole?

25:18.183 --> 25:19.810
- Sometimes, yeah.

25:19.810 --> 25:20.936
- Can you go hang out
with Paige?

25:20.936 --> 25:21.937
- No.
- Please?

25:21.937 --> 25:23.772
- No.

25:23.772 --> 25:25.858
- Are the girls
in high school mean?

25:25.858 --> 25:28.777
- No, everybody's super nice.

25:28.777 --> 25:30.362
- Yeah, I--
I bet you're popular.

25:37.536 --> 25:40.622
- I'm hungry.
Do you want something?

25:40.622 --> 25:43.667
- I'm good.
- Hey, get in line.

25:43.667 --> 25:46.253
We'll, uh, guard the bikes.

25:46.253 --> 25:48.172
- No way.
- I'll pay for your slice.

25:56.138 --> 25:58.515
- Hey, let's go.

25:58.515 --> 26:00.142
- What?

27:20.973 --> 27:22.099
Found one.

27:23.475 --> 27:25.644
Not bad, not bad.
I can do better.

27:27.145 --> 27:28.939
- Hmm, ugly.

27:30.148 --> 27:33.360
It's gone.

27:33.360 --> 27:36.196
Okay, what about this one?

27:36.196 --> 27:37.489
- Better.

27:42.494 --> 27:44.288
So where do you go
to school down there?

27:45.038 --> 27:47.499
- Uh, Old Rochester.

27:47.499 --> 27:50.377
- You like it?

27:50.377 --> 27:52.421
- I actually didn't go there
all last year.

27:52.421 --> 27:56.091
Um, I worked with my dad
on his boats.

27:56.091 --> 27:58.093
He owns tugboats.

27:58.093 --> 27:59.386
- Hmm, that's cool.

27:59.386 --> 28:00.929
- Yeah, it's whatever.

28:04.683 --> 28:05.684
My parents pulled me out.

28:05.684 --> 28:07.477
I, um--I wasn't feeling...

28:10.689 --> 28:12.733
Very good.
I was...

28:22.409 --> 28:26.330
- Is that why you can't sleep?
You don't feel good?

28:28.332 --> 28:29.917
- I'm a thinker.

28:32.461 --> 28:33.712
Me too.

28:35.464 --> 28:37.716
- Yeah?
What you think about?

28:39.885 --> 28:43.263
- I don't know...

28:43.263 --> 28:46.808
Me?

28:46.808 --> 28:51.146
I don't always like me.
Is that weird?

28:52.981 --> 28:56.109
- I was weird enough that I had
to talk to a bunch of doctors.

28:57.861 --> 28:59.696
- I'm weird enough I have to...

29:03.784 --> 29:05.285
- I have to, like...

29:19.299 --> 29:20.759
- That's the one.

29:20.759 --> 29:24.471
- So you remember me
when you go back to Lameville.

29:26.682 --> 29:28.600
- It's not lame.

29:29.309 --> 29:32.312
You should come,
see for yourself.

29:32.312 --> 29:34.648
- What will your boyfriend
think about that?

29:36.066 --> 29:37.943
- I don't have a boyfriend.

29:38.902 --> 29:40.737
- Oh.
Me neither.

29:40.737 --> 29:42.280
- Ha ha.

29:45.742 --> 29:47.452
I've never had a boyfriend.

29:49.997 --> 29:51.331
- That's okay.

29:52.791 --> 29:54.793
I'm not really
dating anybody either.

29:57.963 --> 30:02.050
I'm too much trouble.
- Ooh.

30:02.050 --> 30:03.552
- It's charming, right?

30:04.720 --> 30:06.054
- Kind of.

30:08.807 --> 30:10.517
- Kind of cute?

30:13.478 --> 30:15.439
- You said that already.

31:00.525 --> 31:02.027
- Are you okay?

31:02.027 --> 31:05.697
- Yeah, no, of course.
It's just--it's a lot.

31:05.697 --> 31:09.242
- Okay.

31:09.242 --> 31:10.619
- I like it.

31:11.745 --> 31:12.913
- Me too.

31:14.456 --> 31:17.167
- Gotta go.

31:17.167 --> 31:20.003
- I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to, like--

31:20.003 --> 31:22.756
- No, it's not--

31:22.756 --> 31:24.549
My grandma.

31:24.549 --> 31:26.510
- Yeah, definitely.

31:38.980 --> 31:41.233
- Do you want my number?

31:41.233 --> 31:43.026
- Yeah, if you'll give it.

31:57.582 --> 31:58.959
What time are you
leaving tomorrow?

32:00.085 --> 32:02.003
- 9:00.

32:02.003 --> 32:03.797
I'll come say bye.

32:05.298 --> 32:06.716
- Okay.

32:38.081 --> 32:40.458
You all right?

32:40.458 --> 32:41.710
- Yeah.

32:41.710 --> 32:43.378
You sure?

32:44.296 --> 32:47.883
You--you look all right.
No broken bones, no blood.

32:50.051 --> 32:53.388
- Yeah, I'm fine.
What?

32:53.388 --> 32:54.514
- No, I just thought something

32:54.514 --> 32:55.807
really terrible
must have happened,

32:55.807 --> 32:57.809
since you left your sister
at a pizza shop.

33:09.362 --> 33:10.822
- I went out with a friend.

33:10.822 --> 33:13.658
- Mm-hmm.
You have fun?

33:15.994 --> 33:17.287
- Yeah.
- Good.

33:19.497 --> 33:21.625
- Listen, Dad--
- Shut your mouth.

33:21.625 --> 33:22.959
Take off
those stupid fucking ears.

33:22.959 --> 33:24.252
Take 'em off.

33:25.128 --> 33:29.090
What kind of a man abandons
his little sister?

33:29.090 --> 33:30.300
- I didn't abandon her.
She was fine.

33:30.300 --> 33:31.760
- She had to ask a stranger
to get her here.

33:31.760 --> 33:34.179
D'you know that?
Came home in tears.

33:36.640 --> 33:37.849
You gotta apologize.

33:38.683 --> 33:39.893
- Sorry.

33:39.893 --> 33:41.186
- To your sister, Coco!

33:42.771 --> 33:45.273
Get that look off
your face right now.

33:45.273 --> 33:46.358
Get it off.

33:50.570 --> 33:52.364
Go upstairs,

33:52.364 --> 33:54.491
make it right with Sydney,
and go to bed.

33:57.494 --> 33:58.787
- I'm hungry.

33:58.787 --> 34:00.163
Too bad dinner was at 5:00.

34:00.163 --> 34:01.623
- Dick.

34:01.623 --> 34:05.001
What?
What did you say to me?

34:08.129 --> 34:10.423
What the fuck did you
just say to me?

34:10.423 --> 34:13.343
Say it again.
Say it again, come on.

34:13.343 --> 34:14.636
What?
- I didn't--

34:20.141 --> 34:21.601
- Fuck.

34:36.533 --> 34:39.369
Get the hell out of here,
you fucking narc.

34:42.831 --> 34:45.208
I said get out!

35:01.057 --> 35:03.852
Come on, Michelle.
Let's go.

35:37.344 --> 35:39.012
- Thank you all for coming.

35:40.388 --> 35:43.475
It means so much to see you
all here for Conrad.

35:45.101 --> 35:48.980
These past few weeks
have been very hard.

35:50.649 --> 35:55.278
He was my best friend,
the love of my life.

35:56.905 --> 36:00.158
But I know, with your support,
we will all get through this.

36:02.619 --> 36:04.704
I miss you so much, Conrad.

36:04.704 --> 36:05.955
We love you, Michelle.

36:05.955 --> 36:08.416
Yeah, whoo!

36:12.712 --> 36:14.589
- Conrad was such
a bright light.

36:15.965 --> 36:17.759
He loved baseball.

36:18.510 --> 36:20.053
And I know he'll be
looking down on us

36:20.053 --> 36:23.181
with a smile on his face
as we honor him today.

36:24.057 --> 36:27.894
Now let's go hit
some homers for Conrad.

36:37.654 --> 36:39.239
- Hey, I was gonna
give a speech.

36:39.239 --> 36:42.659
- Oh, I didn't know
you wanted to say anything.

36:43.785 --> 36:45.537
- He was my best friend.

36:46.579 --> 36:49.416
- I'm sorry.
I just--I wasn't thinking.

36:50.333 --> 36:53.670
I just want everything
to go perfect today.

36:57.090 --> 36:58.883
- It's okay.
Never mind.

37:02.178 --> 37:04.180
- That was weird.

37:04.180 --> 37:05.974
- Be nice.

37:11.896 --> 37:14.274
Whoo!

37:17.610 --> 37:19.112
- Yeah.
- Come on, Michelle.

37:29.164 --> 37:30.498
Take your time.
Take your time.

37:32.417 --> 37:34.127
- Ah!

37:38.798 --> 37:40.300
Yes!

38:04.783 --> 38:06.534
Whoo!

38:06.534 --> 38:08.203
Great job, Joey.

38:11.623 --> 38:14.000
- I feel like my heart
is missing.

38:14.000 --> 38:15.752
- I know.

38:15.752 --> 38:19.756
- Lynn, hi.
I'm so glad you made the drive.

38:19.756 --> 38:21.341
- I wouldn't have missed it.

38:21.341 --> 38:25.178
It's so nice for Michelle
to put all this together.

38:25.178 --> 38:26.387
Means a lot.

38:26.387 --> 38:30.141
- Thank you.
I wanted to give you this.

38:30.141 --> 38:33.645
If you need something,
you want to talk.

38:33.645 --> 38:35.188
- What's a staging company?

38:35.188 --> 38:36.898
- Basically,
an interior designer for homes

38:36.898 --> 38:38.441
that are about to go
in the market.

38:38.441 --> 38:40.568
It makes it more appealing
to buyers.

38:40.568 --> 38:42.153
If you ever want to put
your house on the market,

38:42.153 --> 38:44.280
I'd be happy to help.

38:44.280 --> 38:46.115
- I rent.
- Oh.

38:46.115 --> 38:49.619
Well, homeownership
is not for everyone.

38:56.459 --> 39:00.505
Out of curiosity, has Michelle
been in contact with you?

39:01.756 --> 39:05.468
- Yeah, a bit.
Is everything okay?

39:05.468 --> 39:09.180
- She's just so young
to be dealing with all...

39:11.099 --> 39:14.686
I worry about her.

39:14.686 --> 39:17.522
I got our Verizon bill
a couple of days ago,

39:17.522 --> 39:21.943
and she's been texting
your son's phone.

39:23.236 --> 39:25.113
Maybe it's
her grieving process,

39:25.113 --> 39:27.907
but sometimes I worry
that maybe she's hopeful

39:27.907 --> 39:31.452
that he's somehow
going to respond.

39:34.247 --> 39:36.124
I'm--I'm so sorry.
This is a lot.

39:36.124 --> 39:37.625
I shouldn't be
telling you all this.

39:37.625 --> 39:40.211
- Lynn!

39:40.211 --> 39:42.171
Sorry
I didn't say hello earlier.

39:42.171 --> 39:43.548
I've been running around,

39:43.548 --> 39:45.258
trying to make everything
perfect.

39:45.258 --> 39:47.427
- This is
the famous Michelle Carter.

39:48.469 --> 39:50.680
You've done a great job.

39:50.680 --> 39:52.891
- I would do anything
for Conrad.

39:54.934 --> 39:57.103
I'll be over there
if you need me, okay?

39:57.103 --> 39:58.813
- Yeah, thanks, Mom.

39:58.813 --> 40:01.482
Is there anything
I can get you?

40:01.482 --> 40:03.860
- No, I'm just--I'm glad

40:03.860 --> 40:05.820
the kids
are having fun out there.

40:18.207 --> 40:20.793
- That weekend in Florida,

40:20.793 --> 40:23.296
he brought me flowers
the morning I left.

40:24.923 --> 40:28.927
- Coco?
My Coco?

40:28.927 --> 40:31.262
- Flowers?

40:31.262 --> 40:33.723
- Purple lilies.
They were beautiful.

40:33.723 --> 40:35.850
- Huh.

40:35.850 --> 40:39.270
I didn't even know he had
a romantic bone in him.

40:39.270 --> 40:42.315
Guess that skipped
a generation or two.

40:46.778 --> 40:49.572
- We had such deep
conversations, you know,

40:49.572 --> 40:51.532
about our lives, about you.

40:59.290 --> 41:01.542
I was wondering
if you brought that note.

41:02.877 --> 41:04.754
- What?

41:04.754 --> 41:06.339
- The note Conrad left for me.

41:06.339 --> 41:08.800
I texted you about it
a couple of times.

41:08.800 --> 41:11.386
- Oh, no.
I--I don't have it.

41:11.386 --> 41:13.346
- It's totally fine, of course.

41:17.266 --> 41:21.688
- What did he say about me?

41:24.649 --> 41:27.360
You said he talked about me?

41:27.360 --> 41:29.696
- Oh, yeah, he said that--

41:29.696 --> 41:31.406
Dogs!

41:31.406 --> 41:32.991
- Sorry, one second.

41:43.459 --> 41:45.003
YOLO.

41:51.259 --> 41:53.511
- What is that?
- Is it bad?

41:56.180 --> 41:58.808
- So you friends
with Conrad or Michelle?

41:58.808 --> 42:01.519
- Michelle.

42:01.519 --> 42:02.937
She's lucky
to have you.

42:04.564 --> 42:06.107
Did--did you know Conrad?

42:06.107 --> 42:07.442
- Only what she told us.

42:07.442 --> 42:09.193
- Never met him?

42:12.905 --> 42:15.074
I can't imagine what
she's going through right now.

42:15.074 --> 42:16.743
- I know.
It's--it's been brutal.

42:16.743 --> 42:20.288
- Yeah, when he went missing,
she was, like, freaking out.

42:21.581 --> 42:22.915
- Missing?

42:22.915 --> 42:26.210
- Yeah, he was missing
for, like, three days.

42:26.210 --> 42:28.504
- Three days?
You're sure about that?

42:28.504 --> 42:30.506
She was texting us
the whole time.

42:30.506 --> 42:33.885
Said when he wasn't responding,
she knew something was wrong.

42:33.885 --> 42:37.263
She said the family was out
looking for him all weekend.

42:37.263 --> 42:39.891
Even you guys.

42:39.891 --> 42:42.018
- The police?

42:42.018 --> 42:44.812
- Isn't this, like,
something you should know?

42:47.273 --> 42:50.651
- Yeah, yeah, it is.

42:52.361 --> 42:54.030
- Nat! Cass!

42:58.493 --> 43:00.328
- Nice talking to you.
- Yeah.

43:05.958 --> 43:09.295
- Um...

43:09.295 --> 43:11.005
Let's do our own.
Yeah?

43:16.260 --> 43:17.553
- Yeah.

43:17.553 --> 43:19.764
Coming in.
Think I got some good ones.

43:20.640 --> 43:24.977
- Thank you.
- Oh, that's good.

43:24.977 --> 43:26.896
- Cute.

43:29.524 --> 43:33.444
- Hey, so, um,

43:33.444 --> 43:36.572
Conrad was missing
for three days, right?

43:36.572 --> 43:39.408
- Yeah, why?
- Some guy was asking.

43:39.408 --> 43:43.996
- What guy?

43:43.996 --> 43:46.374
- I think he's a cop.

44:06.060 --> 44:10.314
- Michelle?
You okay?

44:10.314 --> 44:12.150
- It's fine.
Yeah, I'm fine.

44:55.610 --> 44:57.486
I'm really proud
of you, Michelle.

44:58.613 --> 45:01.699
- Yeah.

45:01.699 --> 45:04.869
I just have to run in.
I'll be a minute.
